<h3>Setup</h3>

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>place 2 starting tiles vertically, same orientation</li>
                <li>shuffle Patrol cards, discard 1 to box</li>
                <li>add 2 police to each starting tile, return duplicates to bag</li>
                <li>player pawns at hospital</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>$9k</li>
                <li>3 asset tiles with police shields on item spaces</li>
                <li>"extra action" asset tile on the $5k space</li>
                <li>3 remaining asset tiles on contact card spaces</li>
                <li>rest token with sun face up</li>
                <li>random Escape Plan card</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Phases</h3>

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <!-- Income -->
            <h4>1. Income</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Skip on day 1</li>
                <li>Take money based on cubes</li>
                <li>Notoriety 1-2 may spend $3k to unlock an asset tile</li>
            </ul>
            
            <!-- Patrol -->
            <h4>2. Patrol</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Draw 2 cards from patrol deck (1 on day 3)</li>
                <li>place card on corresponding patrol space of the board</li>
                <li>2 cards on patrol space = exit is blocked</li>
                <li>Exit blocked <span class="arrow"></span> place a stack of exit tiles when it appears</li>
            </ul>
            
            <!-- City -->
            <h4>3. City</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Add 4 city tiles to the board, in turn order</li>
                <li>New tiles must touch 2+ existing tiles</li>
                <li>1+ land type of new tile must match an adjacent tile</li>
                <li>All police move with the new tile</li>
                <li>Add an available business or safe house, if necessary</li>
                <li>Add 2 gang members, if necessary</li>
                <li>Reveal next 4 city tiles, add 2 police</li>
                <li>After adding 8 police, return duplicates to bag without replacing</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <!-- Turn order -->
            <h4>4. Turn order</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Most notoriety <span class="arrow"></span> first player</li>
                <li>Descending in order of notoriety</li>
                <li>Tie <span class="arrow"></span> positions are swapped</li>
            </ul>
            
            <!-- Player action -->
            <h4>5. Player Actions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><u>Rest</u> or <u>Move</u></li>
                <li>Rest:
                    <ul>
                        <li>unavailable if rest token is on moon side</li>
                        <li>flip rest token to moon side</li>
                        <li>reset all contact cards, equipment tiles, and first aid token</li>
                        <li>unlock any 1 asset tile</li>
                        <li>may still use executive actions</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Morning, afternoon, evening, night, dawn</li>
                <li>For each part of the day:
                    <ol>
                        <li>players take actions and executive actions in turn order</li>
                        <li>notoriety track is updated in turn order</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Night & dawn optional, requires extra action discs</li>
                <li>Mandatory 3 actions unless escaping early on day 3</li>
                <li>Resolve night in turn order, players act/pass on their turn</li>
                <li>May do action at dawn, independent of night</li>
            </ul>
            <!-- Change of Day -->
            <h4>6. Change of Day</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>skip on day 3</li>
                <li>all rest tokens flip back to sun side</li>
                <li>reset time marker on time track</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Move Action</h3>

<h4>1. Travel</h4>
<ul>
    <li>1-3 movement points</li>
    <li>Corners touching &ne; adjacent</li>
    <li>Must end at a different location from start</li>
    <li>Movement points:
        <ul>
            <li>leave a location</li>
            <li>enter a location</li>
            <li>cross land</li>
            <li>move between locations</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>May spend gas for +1 MP</li>
    <li>F = Ferry, water can be traversed</li>
    <li>Transportation: Subway and Heliport
        <ul>
            <li>if turn begins on 1 of these (or enter it during turn), may use its ability for traveling or leave normally</li>
            <li>Subway: instantly teleport to another subway location without using MP; +1 MP bonus for the turn</li>
            <li>Heliport: spend 1 MP to move directly to any land/location on a city tile 1-2 tiles away</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h4>2. Avoid</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Skip if start/stop locations are both on the <i>same tile</i></li>
    <li>Otherwise: must avoid all police on each tile <i>departed from</i>, but not on destination tile</li>
    <li>Subway/Heliport: avoid police on departure tile, but ignore any "flyovers"</li>
    <li>Need to use executive actions to avoid police</li>
    <li>For any unavoidable police:
        <ul>
            <li>move 1 wound cube from green to red area</li>
            <li>if all cubes are in red area and you need to take another wound:
                <ol>
                    <li>add a handcuff card to right-most space at bottom of player board that does not have handcuffs</li>
                    <li>move 1 cube from red back to green area</li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h4>3. Visit</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Skip if ending movement on Subway/Heliport</li>
</ul>
            
